}}
'''''Here Comes Mr. Jordan''''' is a [1941] comedy film in which a boxer, accidentally killed before his time, is allowed a chance to come back to Earth in the body of a rich man who has just been murdered by his wife.  It stars [Robert Montgomery (actor)|Robert Montgomery], [Evelyn Keyes], [Claude Rains], [Rita Johnson], [Edward Everett Horton], [James Gleason], [John Emery], [Donald MacBride], [Don Costello], [Halliwell Hobbes] and [Benny Rubin].

The movie was adapted by [Sidney Buchman] and [Seton I. Miller] from the play ''Heaven Can Wait'' by [Harry Segall].  It was directed by [Alexander Hall].

It won [Academy Awards] for [Academy Award for Best Story|Best Writing, Original Story] and [Academy Award for Writing Adapted Screenplay|Best Writing, Screenplay].  It was nominated for [Academy Award for Best Actor|Best Actor in a Leading Role] (Robert Montgomery), [Academy Award for Best Supporting Actor|Best Actor in a Supporting Role] (James Gleason), [Academy Award for Best Cinematography|Best Cinematography, Black-and-White], [Academy Award for Directing|Best Director] and [Academy Award for Best Picture|Best Picture].

''Here Comes Mr. Jordan'' was followed up in [1947] by ''[Down to Earth (1947 movie)|Down to Earth]'', in which many of the same characters and actors reprised their roles.

It was remade several times, with different titles:
*''[Heaven Can Wait (1978)|Heaven Can Wait]'' ([1978])
*''[Heaven's Touch]'' ([1983])
*''[Down to Earth (2001 movie)|Down to Earth]'' ([2001])

