    <title>The Pied Piper (1942 film)</title>
      <text xml:space="preserve">'''''The Pied Piper''''' is a [1942] film in which an Englishman, on vacation in [France], is caught up in the [Germany|German] invasion of that country, and finds himself helping a large group of children to safety.  It stars [Monty Woolley], [Roddy McDowall], [Anne Baxter], [Otto Preminger], [J. Carrol Naish], [Lester Matthews], [Jill Esmond], [Ferike Boros] and [Peggy Ann Garner].

The movie was adapted by [Nunnally Johnson] from the novel by [Nevil Shute].  It was directed by [Irving Pichel].

It was nominated for [Academy Awards] for [Academy Award for Best Actor|Best Actor in a Leading Role] (Monty Woolley), [Academy Award for Best Cinematography|Best Cinematography, Black-and-White] and [Academy Award for Best Picture|Best Picture].

