'''''Watch on the Rhine''''' is a [1943] film which tells the story of a man who, in attempting to return to the [United States] during [World War II], is blackmailed by a [Nazi] sympathiser.

The movie was adapted by [Dashiell Hammett] and [Lillian Hellman] from Hellman's play.  It was directed by [Hal Mohr] (uncredited) and [Herman Shumlin].

It won the [Academy Award for Best Actor] (Paul Lukas) and was nominated for [Academy Award for Best Supporting Actress|Best Actress in a Supporting Role] (Lucile Watson), [Academy Award for Best Picture|Best Picture] and [Academy Award for Writing Adapted Screenplay|Best Writing, Screenplay].

